items.title: Desmond's timing disrupted by DL stints
items.summary: Ian Desmond, who turns 32 on Wednesday, has been on the disabled list three times in a disappointing first season with the Rockies.

items.title: Beltran's luck changing with big game vs. M's
items.summary: The first of Carlos Beltran's three hits on Saturday ignited a four-run frame that led to an 8-6 win over Seattle, giving the Astros wins in the first two games of the three-game series.

items.summary: Right-hander Jason Hammel will be haunted by one pitch in Saturday's 8-4 loss to the Indians at Progressive Field.

items.title: Miggy exits with low back tightness
items.summary: The recurring back problems that have bothered Miguel Cabrera for much of the season have returned. The Tigers first baseman left Saturday's game against the White Sox with lower back tightness and is listed as day to day.

items.title: Phils to end season without using lefty starter
items.summary: The Phillies will end this season without having used a single left-handed starter. The last time that happened was 1918.
